{
  "stem": "1033.4",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It is written down.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But, but it has to do with letting go because I was getting really hyper and tense.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Because I've done a lot of this.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I speak for the Holocaust.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I have something else.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I'm writing this story, the three--",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, interestingly through the accumulation of my own years and each season bringing each-- bring-- each season bringing new things to the surface, you could almost say naturally, the types of reflections and the types of sensitivities I, I now possess, were overridden by more immediate concerns, that is, earning a living.",
      "word_count": 52
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] Well, a number of reasons.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "First is that it offends me to think that I'm ashamed that I'm a Jew.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I haven't yet seen a person in this world who wasn't a something.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I am neither more, nor less.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I, too, am a something.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I, I am affiliated to a group of people known as Jews.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "My mother was a Jew-- Jewess.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "My father was Jewish and, and all through the generations.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And knowing a little bit about our history, I don't think comparing our history to anyone's history that I am justified to, to feel ashamed, even though I have deeply absorbed the wounds of pre-Hitler propaganda where I looked for-- I caught myself looking for so-called Jewish traits in my fellow Jews.",
      "word_count": 52
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And, and I find that hurtful.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And this is an aside.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "My entire life is an aside.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I happen to be reading, just now, Sartre's And he shows an amazing insight into human nature, into my-- even into my own nature.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And, and I feel enlightened to, to admit to some of the observations that he makes.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "It also happens that my grandmother's youngest sister's son, who's in Toronto, who has a Jewish wife and two children, they, they became Christians in 1943.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And I see them.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "I love them.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "But they want to have nothing to do with being Jewish.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And their kids married Christian kids.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And that's fine.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "But in a sense, it-- I feel that-- because of them, I feel I want to stand up and say that I'm a Jew.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "Why I haven't talked to my children about this-- when I started working for Ontario Hydro by the name of Scott because I didn't-- certainly, I wasn't [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And I didn't want to call myself Szasz or Spiegel.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "I didn't want them to know I was Jewish.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "I was scared.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "It's understandable.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "I said I was Protestant.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And-- and that was fine.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "But as time went on, I did admit to people who I worked with in Hydro.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "And Hydro was a really boring job, in terms of being mechanical.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "But the people were wonderful.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "I had a couple of Englishmen, a Canadian.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "And they were like brothers to me-- good sense of humor.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "Some of them were in the army in the war.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "And we got along great.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "And I told them that yes, I was Jewish.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "And with-- in terms of having children-- and we lived in Scarborough because I could not afford to live in a Jewish area in Toronto.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "I could have bought a, a, a semi-detached place on Keele Street.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "And, for the same amount of money-- $3,500, which I borrowed from the Ontario Hydro Credit Union-- I managed to get a four-bedroom bungalow at Crocus Drive.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "That's Warden and 401.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "And my three children-- or two of my three children were born there.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "And, and people knew that we were Jewish.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "But I didn't talk about the Holocaust to my children.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "Primarily, in the first instance, they were too-- too young.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "In the second instance, when they got older, I didn't want to weaken them.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "I didn't think that this, in any way, could contribute to them.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 47,
      "text": "My huge-- and to this very moment, inexplicable-- embarrassment with the human race, how these things could, in fact, go on-- and it wasn't one Hitler or, or 10 people, diabolical, got together.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 48,
      "text": "There were tens of thousands of people involved in the-- in the production of, of, of the death factories one way or another, and millions of people who didn't care and didn't want to care.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 49,
      "text": "And even though all along I'm saying that these people are my brothers-- and I do not ever want to forgo them.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 50,
      "text": "And if they're part of me, I must take responsibility for them.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 51,
      "text": "It's a difficult thing to do.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 52,
      "text": "For all these reasons, I didn't talk to my kids about it.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 53,
      "text": "I didn't want them to feel any less than the rest of the kids who they were playing with.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It came by degrees.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "By then, they were married.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they were surprised.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But-- and you will meet them later.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They are wonderful children.",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
